localStorage saves info such that even though you exit the browser it's still saved


four main function:
-get (gets the key's value)
-set (updates the key's value)
-delete (removes the key itself and only the key)
- clear (removes everything in localStorage)

- data in localStorage can be anything that's stringified
- data in localStorage can only be stored as strings

const variables aren't updatable nor redeclarable
const variables once declared will always have the same value

objects can be declared as let
when declared as const:
- the values of its keys can be modified but the keys themselves can't be modified

when declared as let:
-  both the keys and the values of its keys can be modified